682
00:50:19,340 --> 00:50:20,430
And Nina made a successful debut

683
00:50:20,430 --> 00:50:21,570
as my replacement.

684
00:50:22,020 --> 00:50:24,120
When I was living in darkness for three years,

685
00:50:24,390 --> 00:50:27,390
Nina has been shining as a prima ballerina.

686
00:50:27,950 --> 00:50:29,140
Isn't this story

687
00:50:29,770 --> 00:50:31,390
quite dramatic?

688
00:50:32,050 --> 00:50:33,950
Please support generously to our ballet company,

689
00:50:34,420 --> 00:50:36,370
Fantasia, as much as you find

690
00:50:36,660 --> 00:50:38,120
this story entertaining

691
00:50:38,120 --> 00:50:41,160
and as much as you'll share it with others.

692
00:50:48,980 --> 00:50:50,450
I apologize for my long toast.

693
00:50:51,410 --> 00:50:52,730
Enjoy your day today.

694
00:50:52,870 --> 00:50:54,190
No one can be sure

695
00:50:54,410 --> 00:50:55,550
if you'll be okay the next day.

696
00:51:04,080 --> 00:51:06,070
Let go. Let go of me.

697
00:51:09,220 --> 00:51:10,240
Director Choi!

698
00:51:10,380 --> 00:51:12,130
You've crossed the line.

699
00:51:12,170 --> 00:51:13,620
Get your hand off me.

700
00:51:15,350 --> 00:51:17,320
I know that you are rude to the core

701
00:51:17,320 --> 00:51:19,090
and that you do everything you want to do

702
00:51:19,090 --> 00:51:20,840
like a spoiled princess.

703
00:51:21,110 --> 00:51:22,820
But this was just too much.

704
00:51:22,820 --> 00:51:24,590
You should've braced yourself when you had a party

705
00:51:24,590 --> 00:51:26,160
on my parents' death anniversary.

706
00:51:27,980 --> 00:51:29,380
Those people inside are

707
00:51:30,090 --> 00:51:31,930
in the first percentile of this country.

708
00:51:31,930 --> 00:51:34,220
Their seconds and minutes are like gold.

709
00:51:34,220 --> 00:51:35,530
Do you think it's easy

710
00:51:35,530 --> 00:51:36,850
to accommodate their schedules?

711
00:51:37,440 --> 00:51:39,050
What? You're laughing?

712
00:51:41,880 --> 00:51:42,880
Hey.

713
00:51:44,070 --> 00:51:46,050
Since we're at it, let's be frank here.

714
00:51:46,150 --> 00:51:48,440
How have we wronged you?

715
00:51:48,440 --> 00:51:49,660
What do you have against us

716
00:51:49,660 --> 00:51:51,650
to come all the way here and ruin this event?

717
00:51:51,650 --> 00:51:52,780
You smiled.

718
00:51:56,620 --> 00:51:58,240
You smiled that day.

719
00:51:58,380 --> 00:51:59,440
Oh, no!

720
00:51:59,480 --> 00:52:00,670
Yeonseo!

721
00:52:00,970 --> 00:52:01,990
Yeonseo!

722
00:52:15,310 --> 00:52:16,590
Goodness.

723
00:52:17,040 --> 00:52:18,000
Oh, my.

724
00:52:19,890 --> 00:52:21,300
You're unbelievable.

725
00:52:22,360 --> 00:52:24,730
I'm your aunt.

726
00:52:24,820 --> 00:52:26,140
Sure. You could say

727
00:52:28,160 --> 00:52:32,080
that we're a distant cousin.

728
00:52:32,520 --> 00:52:34,550
But we're still a family.

729
00:52:35,590 --> 00:52:37,980
There's a line you can't cross.

730
00:52:39,080 --> 00:52:40,440
I thought you were just blind,

731
00:52:40,440 --> 00:52:42,340
but is it possible that you've gone mad too?

732
00:52:43,660 --> 00:52:44,660
Stop.

733
00:52:46,870 --> 00:52:47,880
What if I don't?

734
00:52:48,350 --> 00:52:50,160
There will be a bigger scene.

735
00:52:56,940 --> 00:52:57,910
Let's go.

736
00:54:33,480 --> 00:54:34,660
You foolish one.

737
00:54:35,620 --> 00:54:37,740
The beautiful dance of your feet

738
00:54:38,270 --> 00:54:40,730
